In just four years, Jimi Hendrix revolutionised the music 
scene with his transcendent sound and explosive stage 
presence. A peacock, poet and perfectionist, he was a true 
original, who restlessly pushed his musical gifts to their 
extremes.

imagine... tells the story of how this shy, former private 
in the 101st Airborne became the greatest rock guitarist of 
all time, using never-before-seen performance footage, home 
movies and family letters.

With contributions from the Hendrix family, Sir Paul McCartney, 
and former band mates Noel Redding and Mitch Mitchell, 
imagine... presents an in-depth look at Hendrix's life and 
career that was tragically cut short at just 27 years old in 
1970.
